org.sbml.jsbml.math.parser

Class FormulaParserLL3ASTNode2

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.sbml.jsbml.math.parser.FormulaParserLL3ASTNode2
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    FormulaParserLL3ASTNode2Constants, IFormulaParser

    public class FormulaParserLL3ASTNode2
extends java.lang.Object
implements IFormulaParser, FormulaParserLL3ASTNode2Constants
    Class used to parse infix mathematical formula and returns a representation of it as an Abstract Syntax Tree (AST).

    Support almost the same syntax as defined in the LibSBML L3 parser. The things not supported for now are the units associated with numbers.

    Since:
    1.0
    Version:
    $Rev: 2385 $
    Author:
    Alexander Dörr, Nicolas Rodriguez, Victor Kofia

    • Method Detail

      • setCaseSensitive

        public void setCaseSensitive(boolean caseSensitive)
        Sets the case sensitivity of the parser, for the mathml elements.

        The default behavior is to be case sensitive, meaning 'cos' would be recognized as the mathematical cosinus but 'Cos', 'cOs' or any other alternatives would be recognized as a name and read as a 'ci' element. If you pass false to this method all the different versions of cos would be recognized as the mathematical cosinus.

        Parameters:
        caseSensitive - boolean to define if the parser should be case sensitive or not.

      • createModulo

        private ASTPiecewiseFunctionNode createModulo(ASTNode2 leftChild,
                                    ASTNode2 rightChild)
        Returns a piecewise ASTNode representing the modulo operation between the left and right child given.

        The formula produced for 'a % b' or modulo(a, b) is 'piecewise(floor(a/b), gt(a/b, 0), ceil(a/b))'

        Parameters:
        leftChild -
        rightChild -
        Returns:
        a piecewise ASTNode representing the modulo operation between the left and right child given.
        See Also:
        "http://sbml.org/Documents/FAQ#Why_can.27t_I_use_the_.3Crem.3E_operator_in_SBML_MathML.3F"
